v36: The Pareto-Lorenz a coefficients were computed using the top shares estimates (from the top 0.05% share within the top 0.5% share): a=1/[1-log(S0.5%/S0.05%)/log(10)].
v37: The inverted Pareto-Lorenz b coefficients were computed from the Pareto-Lorenz a coefficients using the formula b=a/(a-1). Alternatively they can be computed by using directly the top income shares estimates and the formula: b=1/[log(Skx%/Sx%)/log(k)].
